  "texts": [
    "It is worth noting that the SAW-based selection methods in decision-making with soft set theory usually proceed with the help of a notion known as choice value of an alternative.",
    "Let us present this idea, both when the alternatives are evaluated by a soft set and a fuzzy soft set.Definition 24 ([171, 199]) Consider the set X (of objects or alternatives).",
    "In soft set-based decision-making, the choice value of an alternative equals the number of benefit attributes that it possesses. 2.",
    "In fuzzy soft set-based decision-making, the fuzzy choice value of an alternative is the sum of the membership values associated to all attributes for that alternative.",
    "The selected alternative has the shortest distance from the ideal solution and the farthest distance from the negative ideal solution Gray relational analysis [130] GRA Compromise ranking method that owes to gray system theory."
  ]
}